\f0\fs24 \cf0 # Game Systems & Rules\
\
This document defines the core RPG mechanics: stats, damage formulas, status effects, trance/limit break, and high-level design rules.\
\
## Core Stats\
\
Base stats for characters and enemies:\
\
- `HP` \'96 Hit points, health.\
- `MP` \'96 Mana / resource for spells/abilities.\
- `STR` \'96 Physical attack power.\
- `INT` \'96 Magical attack power.\
- `DEX` \'96 Accuracy, evasion, and possibly attack speed.\
- `VIT` \'96 Physical defense and HP scaling.\
- `SPD` \'96 Movement speed, may also affect cast/animation speed slightly.\
- `CRIT_CHANCE` \'96 Chance (0\'961 or percentage) for critical hits.\
- `CRIT_MULT` \'96 Critical damage multiplier (e.g. 1.5x, 2x).\
- `TRANCE_METER` \'96 Gauge for limit break/trance.\
\
Server must own all stat calculations.\
\
## Derived Stats\
\
- `AttackPower` (physical):\
  - Derived from `STR`, equipped weapon, and buffs.\
- `MagicPower`:\
  - Derived from `INT`, equipped staff/wand, and buffs.\
- `Defense`:\
  - Derived from `VIT`, armor, and buffs.\
- `MagicResist`:\
  - Derived from armor, accessories, and buffs.\
- `Evasion`:\
  - Derived from `DEX`, gear, and buffs.\
\
Exact formulas can evolve, but server must encapsulate them in one place for consistency.\
\
## Damage Formulas\
\
### Physical Damage\
\
Pseudo-formula:\
\
```text\
BaseDamage = max(1, (AttackerAttackPower - TargetDefense))\
DamageWithSkill = BaseDamage * SkillMultiplier\
DamageAfterElement = ApplyElementalModifiers(DamageWithSkill, AttackElement, Attacker, Target)\
DamageWithVariance = DamageAfterElement * Random(0.9, 1.1)\
DamageWithCrit = ApplyCrit(DamageWithVariance, CritChance, CritMultiplier)\
FinalDamage = max(1, round(DamageWithCrit))\
}